UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030439329501195T
KW  - General equilibrium
KW  - Exchange rate volatility
KW  - Money and exchange rates
AB  - This paper analyzes the ability of an open-economy version of Lucas's (1990) liquidity model to account for properties of international data. The focus is on the model's ability to account for exchange rate dynamics and measured effects of monetary policy shocks on exchange rates, interest rates, and real activities across countries. The model generates a prediction that a positive domestic monetary innovation is associated with nominal and real currency depreciations. However, the model's predictions with respect to nominal and real exchange rate volatilities are low.
